## 2) Verified high-confidence facts (from accessible sources)

- FFXV launched on PS4/Xbox One (2016), later on Windows (2018), and was directed by Hajime Tabata after reworking from Versus XIII origins.  
- The game combines real-time combat, open-world travel, and a four-man road-trip structure centered on Noctis, Ignis, Gladiolus, and Prompto.  
- `Brotherhood` is a 5-episode ONA (A-1 Pictures) released in 2016.  
- `Kingsglaive` is a CG feature film directed by Takeshi Nozue and tied directly to the fall-of-Insomnia context.  
- In the `Characters of Final Fantasy XV` source, **Talcott Hester is explicitly identified as Jared Hester's grandson** and part of the Lestallum-survivor thread after Insomnia's fall.

